gov.nasa.worldwind
Class BasicDataConfiguration

java.lang.Object
  gov.nasa.worldwind.BasicDataConfiguration
All Implemented Interfaces:
DataConfiguration
Direct Known Subclasses:
CapabilitiesConfiguration, ElevationModelConfiguration, LayerConfiguration
public class BasicDataConfiguration
extends Object
implements DataConfiguration

An implementation of the DataConfiguration interface, which uses an Element as its backing store. Parameter names in query methods are interpreted as XPath queries against the backing Element.

getDateTimeInMillis

public Long getDateTimeInMillis(String paramName,
                                String pattern)
Searches for a date-time element and if found parses the date-time string to a long value indicating the number of milliseconds of the date from the epoch.

Specified by:
getDateTimeInMillis in interface DataConfiguration
Parameters:
paramName - the parameter name.
pattern - the format pattern of the date. See DateFormat for the pattern symbols. The element content must match this format or be directly convertible to a long.
Returns:
